The Senator representing Sokoto East senatorial district at the National Assembly, Dr Ibrahim Abdullahi Gobir has donated N4.5million and 18 seater bus to the victims of fire outbreak in Gada. The inferno had affected a mosque, houses and a nearby market. Gobir made the donation when he condoled with the victims over the incident, a statement by his media aide Bello Mohammed Anka disclosed. It added that the community members expressed appreciation to the lawmaker for his concerns. Sen. Gobir donates to victims of banditry in Sokoto Senator plans to empower retired civil servants Amaechiâ€™s case stalls ministerial screening